text: It was great to meet and speak with @SecRubio at a recent @HouseForeignGOP hearing. Sec. Rubio committed to establishing a regional passport office in Guam. I look forward to working more with him as we deliver for the country and Guam! https://t.co/bYwb5qtxU4

It is with a heavy heart that I join the global community in mourning the loss of His Holiness Pope Francis. His profound dedication to compassion and unity has left a lasting mark on the world. His passing represents a great loss for humanity, as his legacy of love and empathy will continue to impact generations to come.

Thank you to @SecretaryBurgum and @whitehouse for continuing the dialogue between the Territories and Federal government to build bridges to a brighter future for us. Biba!!

Thank you Chairman Walberg for the introduction in the House Committee on Education and Workforce. 

I am honored to serve on the Subcommittee on Early Childhood Elementary and Secondary Education, the Subcommittee on Higher Education and Workforce Development, and the Subcommittee on Workforce Protections, in the 119th Congress. I am excited to advocate for policies that support Guam’s students, workers, and businesses. Biba Guam! 🇬🇺 @EdWorkforceCmte

It was an honor to meet with Department of Energy, Secretary Chris Wright at the Republican Study Committee luncheon.

We had an insightful discussion on advancing energy policies that benefit both the U.S and Guam. I looking forward to collaborating with Secretary Wright to strengthen our island’s energy independence, and advance Guam’s interests.

Yesterday, I was honored to speak with Ambassador Yamada of Japan. We reaffirmed our staunch commitment to deepening U.S.-Japanese relations by enhancing cooperation in tourism, economy, and security in the Indo-Pacific. As key partners in the Pacific, Guam and Japan share a deep history of friendship and mutual interests. I look forward to continuing our strong partnership!

Last week, the House passed my bill, H.R. 522. This piece of legislation will not only support our veterans in Guam, but also cover adaptive vehicle shipping costs for eligible veterans in American Samoa, CNMI, and other remote U.S. regions. https://t.co/9FtczPyCDc

I am proud to announce that the House has passed my bill, the Deliver for Veterans Act. This piece of legislation authorizes the DVA to provide grants that cover the cost of shipping a modified automobile or other conveyance to disabled veterans who served our nation. https://t.co/NglfgMkbXy

Today, I am proud to announce that the House has passed my bill, the Deliver for Veterans Act. This piece of legislation authorizes the DVA to provide grants that cover the cost of shipping modified automobiles or other conveyance to disabled veterans who served our nation.
